    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-30T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-30T07:00:00-05:00" n="850"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d850">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.00/721: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Palmer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-30T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 30, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 30—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s June 29, 7 p.m. At noon today High Commissioner in my presence
                    telephoned Collet at Antioch instructions to point out to Turkish general
                    American rights to property in question and to inform the latter that American
                    Consul General under instructions from Washington now protests against any steps
                    toward dispossession; <pb facs="1047" n="1039" xml:id="pg_1039"/> that American
                    interests concerned could not be dispossessed <hi rend="italic">manu
                        militari</hi> and that Turkish troops must be housed elsewhere.</p>
                <p>I have telegraphed Embassy at Ankara.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Palmer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
